race.comment: Pretty even race but sticking with FROSTED IN TIME (3) who is in great form this time in. Has a win and three placings from four starts, the latest missed a lip when running on hard. Looks hard to beat again. REASONABLE POINT (4) is fitter for two runs back, finishing runner-up fresh before a fair fifth last time at Wagga. Extra trip a plus, down in weight and can bounce back. SHYAMALAN (5) was a debut winner here then sixth at Moe last time when poised in the straight but ran below expectations. Further improved and worth another chance. TURNAQUID (11) is a seasoned mare who has put tougher a string of good runs and deserves to break through. Expected to give a sight. MAGIC LEPRECHAUN (6) wasn't far away last time and will spot a start but wind up strongly.
